<subSubSection id="1DFC3DD229945DA255018C346BEC4DC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C63652C938F51F9B1BA4ADB89B39B804" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8437696BA490125DF2FB55EB91F9B729" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="4A1AF5171A40E0EB27057E7B2BA3E49F" authorityName="Sheng H. Tang" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Petrocosmea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Petrocosmea duyunensis" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="duyunensis">
<emphasis id="1080347D73C769FB56DB2C72AC9EEA5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Petrocosmea duyunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6D3A122C1C6E8922AB92DFA9AD2F61C1" genus="P." lsidName="P. leiandra" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="leiandra">
<emphasis id="13B2F80886F95D72F1290141DBFE6937" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. leiandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of leaf blades and corolla limb, and in the indumentum of peduncles, calyx, and ovary. However, it differs from the latter in the following characteristics: apex of abaxial lip lobes of corolla acute and reflexed (
<emphasis id="0695DBF8469F66F2CF464639D8E37441" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vs.</emphasis>
round and not reflexed), filaments densely glandular puberulent (
<emphasis id="F1E8BE5D81D06719F92DBEAA65DD84E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vs.</emphasis>
glabrous or sparsely pilose), pistil 4.7-5.8 mm long, included (
<emphasis id="47623BD2C27C08AA6371B79BD4391179" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vs.</emphasis>
ca. 9 mm long, exserted), ovary ovoid (
<emphasis id="5B4ECF2B598001823FD458155A45EC15" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vs.</emphasis>
narrowly ovoid), style distinctly curved, sparsely glandular puberulent, and 2.7-3.7 mm long (
<emphasis id="A5C19E32C251BC94993B335D88DEA1AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vs.</emphasis>
slightly curved, glabrous, and ca. 7 mm long).
</paragraph>
<caption id="723996EE5306127DE899C53CED6111A4" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.181.68635.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578080" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="7C885F7C3592291382A49D84063EC3BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="ADF8B6C18A8BBA11C74EFADA1929F14C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 1.</emphasis>
